==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: rotenone
<hw>ro"te*none</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A chemical
substance (<chform>C23H22O6</chform>) extracted from the root of the
<prodby>derris</prodby> (<spn>Derris elliptica</spn>, <spn>Derris
malaccensis</spn>, and other species), used in treatment of scabies and
as an insecticide for external infestation by chiggers in human
medicine, and in veterinary medicine for the treatment of infestations
with fleas, ticks, and lice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>rotgut</ent>⟦br⟧
